        <!-- Getting Started -->
        <div id="doc-getting-started" class="doc-content active">
            <h3>Getting Started with Akhfhid Bot</h3>
            <p>
                Follow these simple steps to get Akhfhid Bot up and running in
                your server.
            </p>
            <ol>
                <li>
                    <strong>Invite the Bot:</strong> Click the "Invite to
                    Server" button on the home page and select your server.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Grant Permissions:</strong> Make sure the bot has
                    the necessary permissions to read and send messages, connect
                    to voice channels, etc.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Run a Command:</strong> Try typing
                    <code>!help</code> in any channel to see the list of
                    available commands.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Explore Features:</strong> Check out the music,
                    moderation, and fun features to make your server more
                    engaging!
                </li>
            </ol>
        </div>

        <!-- Command List -->
        <div id="doc-command-list" class="doc-content">
            <h3>Command List</h3>
            <p>
                Here are all the commands you can use with the Akhfhid bot:
            </p>

            <div class="command-category">
                <h4><i class="fas fa-robot"></i> AI & Utility Commands</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <code>!chat [message]</code> — Chat with Akhfhid AI.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <code>!airesearch [topic]</code> — Perform in-depth
                        research using AI.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <code>!plex [query]</code> — Search for information with
                        Perplexity AI.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <code>!roblox [username]</code> — Check complete Roblox
                        user information.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <code>!help</code> — Displays a list of all available
                        commands.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <code>!ping</code> — Check the bot's response speed.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <code>!reqfitur [message]</code> — Send a feature request
                        to a dedicated channel.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="command-category">
                <h4><i class="fas fa-trophy"></i> Leveling Commands</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <code>!leaderboard</code> — Displays the top 10 users with
                        the highest level in the server.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <code>!level [@user]</code> — View your or another user's
                        level and XP.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="command-category">
                <h4><i class="fas fa-music"></i> Music Commands</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <code>!play [song name]</code> — Play a song or add it to
                        the queue.
                    </li>
                    <li><code>!queue</code> — Displays the music queue.</li>
                    <li>
                        <code>!skip</code> — Skips the currently playing song.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <code>!stop</code> — Stops the song and clears the queue.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="command-category">
                <h4>
                    <i class="fas fa-shield-alt"></i> Admin & Moderation
                    Commands
                </h4>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <code>!maintenance [message]</code> — Send a maintenance
                        announcement to a specific channel.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <code>!maintdone [message]</code> — Send an announcement
                        that maintenance is complete to all servers.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <code>!setschedule</code> — Configure the daily schedule
                        channel and status.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <code>!welcome [#channel]</code> — Configure the server's
                        welcome message channel.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="command-category">
                <h4>
                    <i class="fas fa-info-circle"></i> Information Commands
                </h4>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <code>!serverinfo</code> — Shows information about the
                        server.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <code>!userinfo [@user]</code> — Displays detailed
                        information about a user.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="command-category">
                <h4><i class="fas fa-code"></i> Aliases</h4>
                <p>
                    Some commands have aliases (short names) for easier use:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <code>!ai</code> ➤ <code>!gpt</code>, <code>!chat</code>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <code>!airesearch</code> ➤ <code>!ai</code>,
                        <code>!research</code>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <code>!help</code> ➤ <code>!h</code>,
                        <code>!commands</code>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <code>!leaderboard</code> ➤ <code>!top</code>,
                        <code>!lb</code>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <code>!level</code> ➤ <code>!rank</code>,
                        <code>!lvl</code>
                    </li>
                    <li><code>!maintenance</code> ➤ <code>!maint</code></li>
                    <li><code>!maintdone</code> ➤ <code>!mdone</code></li>
                    <li>
                        <code>!perplexity</code> ➤ <code>!plex</code>,
                        <code>!ai-plex</code>
                    </li>
                    <!-- <li>
            <code>!ping</code> ➤ <code>!p</code>,
            <code>!latency</code>
          </li> -->
                    <li><code>!play</code> ➤ <code>!p</code></li>
                    <li><code>!queue</code> ➤ <code>!q</code></li>
                    <li>
                        <code>!serverinfo</code> ➤ <code>!si</code>,
                        <code>!server</code>
                    </li>
                    <li><code>!setschedule</code> ➤ <code>!setsch</code></li>
                    <li><code>!skip</code> ➤ <code>!s</code></li>
                    <li><code>!stop</code> ➤ <code>!st</code></li>
                    <li>
                        <code>!userinfo</code> ➤ <code>!ui</code>,
                        <code>!whois</code>
                    </li>
                    <li><code>!welcome</code> ➤ <code>!w</code></li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>

